body:
`SKData.AsStream` returns corrupted images, not all the time, but once in a few tries. Tested on iOS (emulator). 

```C#
using (var image = SKImage.FromBitmap(bitmap))
using (var data = image.Encode(SKImageEncodeFormat.Png, 80))
{
	var stream = data?.AsStream();
	// then process encoded PNG - sometimes is corrupted
}
```

However, this is working just fine (without any issues):

```C#
using (var image = SKImage.FromBitmap(bitmap))
using (var data = image.Encode(SKImageEncodeFormat.Png, 80))
{
	var stream = new MemoryStream();
	data.SaveTo(stream);
	stream.Position = 0;
	// then process encoded PNG - without any issues
}
```

Full code here: https://github.com/luberda-molinet/FFImageLoading/blob/master/source/FFImageLoading.Svg.Shared/SvgDataResolver.cs#L80-L98
